inate, Germany","Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France","Großheppach, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Großheppach, Weinstadt, Rems-Murr-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany","Rheinland-Pfalz, Allemagne":"Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany","Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Française":"Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"SCHWEIKHARDT","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Schweickert  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Schweickert","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ewald, Hans.","German (mainly Württemberg and Bavaria): from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>swinth</i> ‘strong, fast’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’; the <i>-t</i> is epenthetic."]},{"name":"Swigart","meanings":["Perhaps an Americanized form of German   Schweighardt  , <b>Zweigert</b> (see   Swigert  ), or   Sweigard  ."]}]},{"name":"Maria","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Maria  , of German origin but now also moderately popular in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Elisabetha","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament.  See  <b>Elizabeth</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Elizabeth","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Maria Elisabetha SCHWEIKHARDT was born in 1485, in Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany as the daughter of Bartholmé SCHWEIKHARDT. She married Jean Jacques KIEFFER on 28 February 1530, in Zweibrücken, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1560, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1485–1560":"1485–1560","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1500–1560":"1500–1560","1505–1587":"1505–1587","1450–Male":"1450–Surnud","28 February 1530":"28. veebruar 1530","1500":"1500","1587":"1587","Abt 1540":"umbes 1540","1485":"1485","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","1505":"1505","Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Allemagne":"Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Prantsusmaa","Großheppach, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Großheppach, Weinstadt, Rems-Murr-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Rheinland-Pfalz, Allemagne":"Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Française":"Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1485–1560":"1485–1560","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1500–1560":"1500–1560","1505–1587":"1505–1587","1450–Male":"1450–Kuollut","28 February 1530":"28. helmikuuta 1530","1500":"1500","1587":"1587","Abt 1540":"noin 1540","1485":"1485","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","1505":"1505","Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Allemagne":"Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksa","Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Ranska","Großheppach, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Großheppach, Weinstadt, Rems-Murr-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksa","Rheinland-Pfalz, Allemagne":"Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksa","Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Française":"Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Ranska"},"fr":{"1485–1560":"1485–1560","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1500–1560":"1500–1560","1505–1587":"1505–1587","1450–Male":"1450–Décédé","28 February 1530":"28 février 1530","1500":"1500","1587":"1587